cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.RO 

The paper deals with sequential decision making and stochastic control, which are core topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a fast multiscale procedure for compressing Markov decision processes (MDPs) and emphasizes transfer learning across different problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves optimization and decision making, which are relevant to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.RO (Robotics).
